           <h1> On the Road, in the Sky</h1>
          <h2>Drive Less</h2>
          <p>Going carless for a year could save about 2.6 tons of carbon dioxide, according to 2017 study from researchers at Lund University and the University of British Columbia — that’s a little more than a roundtrip transatlantic flight. How can you stop using a car? Try taking a train, bus or better yet, ride a bike.In November 2017 carbon dioxide emissions from transportation surpassed emissions from electricity generation as the top source of greenhouse gases.  Why? Electricity generation is shifting away from the use of coal to more renewable sources and natural gas. </p>
        </div>
         
        <div class="ul-1">
           <h2>Some ways to reduce Carbon footprint: </h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Go easy on the gas and brakes Go easy on the gas and brakes </li>
            <li>Regularly service your car</li>
            <li>Check your tires.  </li>
          
          <li>Air conditioning and intensive city driving</li>
          <li>Use cruise control </li>
          <li>Don’t weigh your car down.</li>
          <li>Carpool </li>
          </ul>
         
