          <h1> On Your Plate</h1>
          <h2>Eat Less Meat</h2>
          <p>While food systems are complicated, and research is still evolving on what the most environmentally-friendly diet is, experts mostly agree that cutting down on meat, and red meat in particular, is a better choice for the environment. This is because the production of red meat uses a lot of feed, water and land.For that reason, eating a vegan diet is likely to be best for the environment, say experts.Eating a vegetarian or pescetarian diet are also likely to be better for the environment than a diet which includes a lot of meat.</p>
